#. <section class="sutta" id="sn22.47"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.47:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.47:0.2"
msgid "5. Attadīpavagga"
msgstr "5. Be Your Own Island"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.47:0.3"
msgid "47. Samanupassanāsutta"
msgstr "47. Ways of Regarding"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn22.47:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn22.47:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Ye hi keci, bhikkhave, samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā anekavihitaṃ attānaṃ "
"samanupassamānā samanupassanti, sabbete pañcupādānakkhandhe samanupassanti, "
"etesaṃ vā aññataraṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, whatever ascetics and brahmins regard various kinds of things "
"as self, all regard the five grasping aggregates, or one of them."

msgctxt "sn22.47:1.3"
msgid "Katame pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "sn22.47:1.4"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano ariyānaṃ adassāvī ariyadhammassa "
"akovido ariyadhamme avinīto, sappurisānaṃ adassāvī sappurisadhammassa "
"akovido sappurisadhamme avinīto "
msgstr ""
"It’s when an uneducated ordinary person has not seen the noble ones, and is "
"neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of the noble ones. They’ve not "
"seen good persons, and are neither skilled nor trained in the teaching of "
"the good persons. "

msgctxt "sn22.47:1.5"
msgid ""
"rūpaṃ attato samanupassati, rūpavantaṃ vā attānaṃ; attani vā rūpaṃ, rūpasmiṃ "
"vā attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They regard form as self, self as having form, form in self, or self in form."

msgctxt "sn22.47:1.6"
msgid "Vedanaṃ …"
msgstr "They regard feeling …"

msgctxt "sn22.47:1.7"
msgid "saññaṃ …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn22.47:1.8"
msgid "saṅkhāre …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn22.47:1.9"
msgid ""
"viññāṇaṃ attato samanupassati, viññāṇavantaṃ vā attānaṃ; attani vā viññāṇaṃ, "
"viññāṇasmiṃ vā attānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"consciousness as self, self as having consciousness, consciousness in self, "
"or self in consciousness."

# See BB’s note.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: avigataṃ → adhigataṃ (bahūsu)
msgctxt "sn22.47:2.1"
msgid "Iti ayañceva samanupassanā ‘asmī’ti cassa avigataṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"So they’re not rid of this way of regarding things and the conceit ‘I am’."

msgctxt "sn22.47:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘Asmī’ti kho pana, bhikkhave, avigate pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ avakkanti hoti—"
msgstr ""
"As long as they’re not rid of the conceit ‘I am’, the five faculties are "
"conceived—"

msgctxt "sn22.47:2.3"
msgid ""
"cakkhundriyassa sotindriyassa ghānindriyassa jivhindriyassa kāyindriyassa."
msgstr "the eye, ear, nose, tongue, and body."

msgctxt "sn22.47:2.4"
msgid "Atthi, bhikkhave, mano, atthi dhammā, atthi avijjādhātu."
msgstr "The mind, thoughts, and the element of ignorance are all present."

msgctxt "sn22.47:2.5"
msgid ""
"Avijjāsamphassajena, bhikkhave, vedayitena phuṭṭhassa assutavato "
"puthujjanassa ‘asmī’tipissa hoti;"
msgstr ""
"Struck by feelings born of contact with ignorance, an uneducated ordinary "
"person thinks ‘I am’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:2.6"
msgid "‘ayamahamasmī’tipissa hoti;"
msgstr "‘I am this’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:2.7"
msgid "‘bhavissan’tipissa hoti;"
msgstr "‘I will be’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:2.8"
msgid "‘na bhavissan’tipissa hoti;"
msgstr "‘I will not be’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:2.9"
msgid "‘rūpī bhavissan’tipissa hoti;"
msgstr "‘I will have form’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:2.10"
msgid "‘arūpī bhavissan’tipissa hoti;"
msgstr "‘I will be formless’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:2.11"
msgid "‘saññī bhavissan’tipissa hoti;"
msgstr "‘I will be percipient’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:2.12"
msgid "‘asaññī bhavissan’tipissa hoti;"
msgstr "‘I will not be percipient’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:2.13"
msgid "‘nevasaññīnāsaññī bhavissan’tipissa hoti."
msgstr "‘I will be neither percipient nor non-percipient’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.47"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: Tiṭṭhanteva kho → tiṭṭhanti kho pana (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: tattheva → tatheva (katthaci)
msgctxt "sn22.47:3.1"
msgid "Tiṭṭhanteva kho, bhikkhave, tattheva pañcindriyāni."
msgstr "The five faculties stay right where they are."

msgctxt "sn22.47:3.2"
msgid "Athettha sutavato ariyasāvakassa avijjā pahīyati, vijjā uppajjati."
msgstr ""
"But an educated noble disciple gives up ignorance about them and gives rise "
"to knowledge."

msgctxt "sn22.47:3.3"
msgid "Tassa avijjāvirāgā vijjuppādā ‘asmī’tipissa na hoti;"
msgstr ""
"With the fading away of ignorance and the arising of knowledge, they don’t "
"think ‘I am’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:3.4"
msgid "‘ayamahamasmī’tipissa na hoti;"
msgstr "‘I am this’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:3.5"
msgid "‘bhavissan’ti …"
msgstr "‘I will be’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:3.6"
msgid "‘na bhavissan’ti …"
msgstr "‘I will not be’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:3.7"
msgid "rūpī …"
msgstr "‘I will have form’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:3.8"
msgid "arūpī …"
msgstr "‘I will be formless’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:3.9"
msgid "saññī …"
msgstr "‘I will be percipient’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:3.10"
msgid "asaññī …"
msgstr "‘I will be non-percipient’,"

msgctxt "sn22.47:3.11"
msgid "‘nevasaññīnāsaññī bhavissan’tipissa na hotī”ti."
msgstr "‘I will be neither percipient nor non-percipient’.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.47:3.12"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
